WEBVTT

00:09.154 --> 00:10.235
Good to be with you this morning.

00:10.275 --> 00:12.237
Thank you for taking the time to tune in.

00:13.058 --> 00:14.700
I'm gonna bring God's word to you this morning.

00:15.140 --> 00:20.325
And my message to you this morning is God's love, a life in you.

00:20.346 --> 00:24.490
I want to encourage you this morning with the message of God's love.

00:25.331 --> 00:28.274
And if you're watching this morning, you haven't put faith in Jesus.

00:28.434 --> 00:33.919
I urge you to listen in because there's some wonderful truths in here for you this morning also.

00:34.540 --> 00:36.402
For the believer in Christ,

00:36.674 --> 00:54.354
I desire that, and I pray that you'll strengthen in your faith this morning, that you'll deepen in your walk with God, that you'll get a greater sense of God's love for you, that you'll find freedom from fear, from anxiety, freedom from inadequacy, freedom from condemnation.

00:55.555 --> 01:02.823
I pray that you would experience a greater unity with God's people through coming to understand more about the love of God this morning.

01:04.285 --> 01:05.586
Let me pray for you.

01:06.050 --> 01:07.772
from Ephesians chapter three.

01:09.755 --> 01:27.897
I pray that God's glorious unlimited resources will empower you within a strength today through God's spirit, that Christ will make his home in your hearts as you trust him, that your roots will grow down into God's love and keep you strong.

01:28.478 --> 01:35.186
And may you have the power to understand, as all God's people should, how wide and how long and how high

01:35.266 --> 01:37.128
and how deep is the love of God.

01:38.610 --> 01:43.997
May you today experience the love of Christ, though it is too great to understand fully.

01:44.978 --> 01:51.446
Then you will be made complete with all the fullness of life and power that comes from God.

01:52.107 --> 01:52.567
Amen.

01:52.587 --> 01:56.032
Are you ready to grasp the love of God with me today?

01:56.913 --> 02:01.298
My first thought for you today is that God is love.

02:02.370 --> 02:03.011
God is love.

02:03.031 --> 02:05.213
He doesn't just show love, but he is love.

02:06.235 --> 02:10.120
We must acknowledge that the love of God is something magnificent.

02:10.180 --> 02:12.182
It's something unexplainable.

02:12.442 --> 02:15.366
It's something truly incomprehensible.

02:16.087 --> 02:22.455
There's so many facets to the love of God that it would take many lifetimes to explore.

02:23.776 --> 02:28.402
But one facet is that the love of God is eternal.

02:29.474 --> 02:34.581
that existed before the world was made and it will exist after this world is long gone.

02:36.223 --> 02:45.996
In John 1724, Jesus speaks to his father of the glory that you've given me and your love for me before the foundation of the world.

02:47.038 --> 02:50.963
The love of the father was shown to Jesus before this world was ever here.

02:52.245 --> 02:56.210
And their love between one to another continues even in the present.

02:56.642 --> 03:02.408
In John 3.25, it says, the Father loves the Son and has given all things into His hand.

03:03.849 --> 03:11.076
And John 14.31, I do as the Father has commanded me so that the world may know that I love the Father.

03:12.237 --> 03:19.764
Isn't it wonderful that there's this unconditional love that exists between the Father and the Son and presumably between the Holy Spirit also?

03:21.065 --> 03:25.810
And I want to hone in now on some of the more practical aspects of the love of God.

03:26.338 --> 03:39.658
because this love that is with God, it wants to be and has been shed abroad in our hearts who trust Christ and we know of His love and the love of God is given and shown toward the world.

03:40.099 --> 03:40.860
And we're gonna look at that.

03:40.900 --> 03:43.885
We see that in 1 John 4, 9 and 10.

03:44.806 --> 03:53.259
This is the love of God that was made manifest among us that God sent His Son into the world so that we might live through Him in this is love.

03:53.740 --> 03:55.122
Not that we have loved God,

03:55.522 --> 04:00.590
but that He loved us and sent His Son to be the propitiation for our sins.

04:02.513 --> 04:06.099
I want you to receive the love of God this morning without hindrance.

04:06.881 --> 04:11.729
Open your heart to receive this wonderful gift without trying to earn it.

04:12.870 --> 04:19.922
Romans 5 and 8, God shows His love for us in this while we were sinners Christ died for us.

04:20.386 --> 04:31.701
And of course, John 3, 16, for God so loved the world that he gave his only son, who so ever would believe in him, would not perish, but have eternal life.

04:33.564 --> 04:41.174
And the Apostle Paul in Galatians 2, 20 says, the son of God who loved me and gave himself for me.

04:41.414 --> 04:44.218
God loves you this morning unconditionally.

04:44.478 --> 04:45.660
His love is toward you.

04:48.023 --> 04:50.066
I see that there's two barriers.

04:50.626 --> 04:59.017
to receiving the love of God, because it's one thing to know about it, to hear about it, but are we really receiving that unconditional love into our hearts?

05:00.398 --> 05:04.924
I think oftentimes inadequacy gets in the way and condemnation can get in the way.

05:06.166 --> 05:11.052
This thing about inadequacy, you know, I'm not good enough for God's love, so I've got to earn his love.

05:12.013 --> 05:16.058
Maybe don't think about it, it's maybe not on the forefront of our minds, but is it subconsciously there?

05:16.499 --> 05:19.122
And our actions and our attitudes towards God

05:19.394 --> 05:22.878
and towards people, and is that inadequacy there?

05:23.279 --> 05:25.802
Can we look at this this morning?

05:25.982 --> 05:34.733
Can we step over that this morning and allow God's unconditional love to just wipe away that inadequacy, that sense of inadequacy that you may feel?

05:36.856 --> 05:48.210
Because in 1 John 4, 16, it says, God is love, and whoever abides in love abides in God, and God abides in Him, by this is love perfected with us.

05:48.418 --> 05:56.046
So we may have confidence for the day of judgment because as he is, so are we in this world.

05:57.307 --> 06:00.130
If you love God this morning, God abides in you.

06:00.190 --> 06:01.711
You don't need to earn it.

06:02.132 --> 06:03.113
You don't need to prove it.

06:04.014 --> 06:05.896
His love abides in you and buy it.

06:05.936 --> 06:06.897
Love is perfected.

06:07.397 --> 06:11.601
You can have confidence today before God because his love abides in you.

06:12.442 --> 06:16.146
And as Christ is righteous and as he is holy and accepted,

06:16.674 --> 06:18.956
You also are accepted before God.

06:19.537 --> 06:21.299
You're loved and you're accepted.

06:21.339 --> 06:23.581
You're more than enough through Christ.

06:24.122 --> 06:25.023
You're not inadequate.

06:25.663 --> 06:27.966
So let's step over that barrier together this morning.

06:30.248 --> 06:31.530
What about condemnation?

06:31.550 --> 06:35.314
This idea that I no longer qualify for God's love.

06:37.015 --> 06:43.282
We know that Romans 8 and 1 says that there is therefore now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

06:43.618 --> 06:47.603
But why do we oftentimes get this sense of condemnation when we've done wrong?

06:47.983 --> 06:50.527
Why do we feel or think condemnation?

06:52.790 --> 07:00.960
Well, 1 John 20 says, for whenever our heart condemns us, God is greater than our heart than he knows everything.

07:01.521 --> 07:05.906
Beloved, if our heart does not condemn us, we have confidence toward God.

07:06.786 --> 07:09.049
Do you often get a sense that your heart's condemning you?

07:09.069 --> 07:12.675
Do you feel self-condemnation because of something wrong that you've done?

07:13.035 --> 07:13.736
That's normal.

07:13.777 --> 07:14.998
We all feel a lot of times.

07:15.659 --> 07:17.542
But God is greater than our heart.

07:19.024 --> 07:21.328
Let God be greater than your heart this morning.

07:22.470 --> 07:23.531
He knows everything.

07:23.832 --> 07:28.098
Beloved, if our heart does not condemn us, we have confidence toward God.

07:28.839 --> 07:32.785
Let's allow God's love in this morning.

07:32.805 --> 07:34.267
Let's refuse condemnation.

07:34.327 --> 07:36.050
Let's have confidence toward God.

07:37.890 --> 07:40.233
Let's step over these barriers together this morning.

07:42.476 --> 07:56.455
We're talking about receiving God's love, and now we want to speak to you about reciprocating God's love, walking in His love, through loving God back with that love that He's given us, and loving others with that love that He's given us.

07:57.617 --> 08:00.521
In Deuteronomy 6, Moses instructs the Israelites.

08:01.502 --> 08:04.286
Hero Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord is one.

08:04.926 --> 08:07.570
You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart,

08:07.714 --> 08:10.418
with all your soul and with all your strength.

08:12.220 --> 08:17.208
We are to reciprocate God's love back to Him with our entire being.

08:18.710 --> 08:20.813
In Deuteronomy, it was under the law.

08:20.933 --> 08:24.698
It was about trying to love God in human strength.

08:25.459 --> 08:26.521
It was striving.

08:26.561 --> 08:27.562
It was self-effort.

08:27.602 --> 08:30.226
It was trying very hard to keep the commandments.

08:32.258 --> 08:35.843
But in the Gospel of Mark, Jesus is questioned on the same thing.

08:35.883 --> 08:39.588
A local scribe asks, which commandment is the most important?

08:39.648 --> 08:45.175
And in response, Jesus says, the most important is hero, Israel, the Lord our God, the Lord is one.

08:45.556 --> 08:52.665
You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your soul, and with all your mind, and with all your strength.

08:53.346 --> 08:56.390
The second is this, you shall love your neighbor as yourself.

08:56.871 --> 08:59.154
There is no commandment greater than these.

09:00.315 --> 09:02.258
Notice how in Mark, Jesus,

09:02.434 --> 09:04.156
adds the words with all your mind.

09:05.517 --> 09:09.602
You know, under the law, it was about strength.

09:11.044 --> 09:14.027
And under grace, it's about renewing the mind.

09:14.548 --> 09:15.249
We're in grace.

09:15.469 --> 09:19.093
We're in the dispensation of grace if you know the Lord this morning.

09:19.173 --> 09:20.094
We're not under the law.

09:21.716 --> 09:24.799
It's not about striving to obey the commands.

09:25.300 --> 09:30.706
It's about letting God's love in, loving Him back, and allowing His love

09:31.010 --> 09:32.571
to lead us to obedience.

09:34.613 --> 09:46.044
You know, in the Greek that word with all your mind, the word mind is dianoia, which simply means a thinking through, a meditating on God.

09:48.307 --> 09:50.368
It's about renewing the mind.

09:51.470 --> 10:00.338
It's about allowing God to work as much as you can through prayer, through praise, through scripture reading.

10:00.770 --> 10:03.313
Jesus said, love the Lord your God with all your heart.

10:04.315 --> 10:06.037
We can pray with our hearts.

10:06.598 --> 10:08.260
Love the Lord your God with all your soul.

10:08.300 --> 10:10.803
We can praise, we can use our lips, we can use our body.

10:11.244 --> 10:12.025
We can praise him.

10:12.686 --> 10:14.368
Love the Lord your God with all your mind.

10:14.869 --> 10:18.694
Remember, Diahania thinking on God through his word.

10:19.735 --> 10:21.498
Love the Lord your God with all your strength.

10:22.039 --> 10:23.440
There is a strength aspect.

10:25.283 --> 10:26.585
It's fighting for prayer.

10:26.645 --> 10:28.367
It's fighting for that time in the word.

10:28.407 --> 10:30.610
It's giving your time

10:30.690 --> 10:31.972
and your energy to the Lord.

10:32.252 --> 10:34.775
It's praising and thanking him when you don't feel like it.

10:38.159 --> 10:44.287
But it's not a reliance on strength, sheer strength and willpower alone to obey God.

10:45.148 --> 10:47.291
No, the Israelites, they tried that and they failed.

10:48.152 --> 10:48.893
We need grace.

10:49.234 --> 10:50.856
We need the love of God.

10:50.916 --> 10:56.763
We need the power of the Holy Spirit to reciprocate God's love back to him and to walk in obedience.

10:57.664 --> 10:59.026
1 John 5 and 3.

10:59.234 --> 11:02.238
If we love God, we will obey His commands.

11:04.021 --> 11:06.905
Romans 13 and 10, love does no wrong to a neighbor.

11:06.965 --> 11:09.870
Therefore love is the fulfilling of the law.

11:11.312 --> 11:13.435
Let's commit today to loving God back.

11:14.537 --> 11:15.879
Let's deepen our prayer life.

11:15.919 --> 11:17.501
Let's learn how to praise Him.

11:17.561 --> 11:20.786
Let's choose thankfulness instead of complaining.

11:21.567 --> 11:26.354
Let's renew our minds through scripture reading, through Bible meditation this morning.

11:27.554 --> 11:36.027
So yes, the love of God is reciprocated back to God, but the love of God is reciprocated to our neighbor, to our loved ones, to people in our world.

11:39.312 --> 11:40.714
Let me read from you.

11:41.535 --> 11:45.541
Let me read to you from 1 Corinthians 13 and 1.

11:46.202 --> 11:52.452
If I speak in the tongues of man and of angels but have not love, I am a noisy gong or a clanging symbol.

11:53.013 --> 11:56.658
If I have prophetic powers and understand all mysteries and all knowledge,

11:56.866 --> 12:01.631
And if I have all faith even to move mountains but have not love, I am nothing.

12:02.472 --> 12:09.039
If I give away all I have, if I deliver up my body to be burnt but have not love, I gain nothing.

12:10.621 --> 12:12.062
And on and on, it goes.

12:13.364 --> 12:14.245
Talking about love.

12:14.345 --> 12:17.728
Yes, love is to be given and shown to award others.

12:19.711 --> 12:22.113
Let me just bring in a couple of small points here.

12:22.133 --> 12:26.578
I think developing relationships is important here.

12:26.722 --> 12:29.946
because to reciprocate the love of God, you need people in your life.

12:31.368 --> 12:43.763
We've all got a responsibility as Christians to develop friendships, to reach out, to send a text message, to Zoom call somebody, to meet with someone for a walk in the park.

12:44.564 --> 12:50.291
It's vital that as Christians that we build relationships, we're part of a worldwide family.

12:51.472 --> 12:56.498
Surely we can make time for three or four people in our life, to confide in

12:56.706 --> 13:01.913
to be accountable to, to pray with, to encourage and to love.

13:03.015 --> 13:05.137
Hebrews 10, 24 to 25.

13:05.898 --> 13:09.523
Let us consider how to stir up one another to love and good works.

13:10.064 --> 13:17.895
Not neglecting to meet together as is the habit of some, but encouraging one another and all the more as you see the day drawing near.

13:17.915 --> 13:20.218
1 John 4, 11.

13:20.538 --> 13:26.226
Beloved, if God loves us, we also ought to love one another.

13:27.010 --> 13:31.777
Let's commit today to developing relationships with fellow believers.

13:33.300 --> 13:34.421
What about forgiveness?

13:35.122 --> 13:38.728
Forgiveness is so important to showing the love of God to others.

13:40.430 --> 13:42.033
Matthew 18, 21 and 22.

13:42.894 --> 13:47.401
Peter came up and said to Jesus, Lord, how often will my brother sin against me?

13:47.441 --> 13:50.065
And I forgive him as many as seven times.

13:50.205 --> 13:53.490
And that sounds like a lot to forgive someone seven times.

13:54.786 --> 13:59.132
And Jesus said to him, I do not say to you seven times, but 77 times.

13:59.613 --> 14:02.957
That's how amazing the forgiveness of God is.

14:03.498 --> 14:13.371
And that's how great the love of God should be in our hearts that we are willing to show that wonderful forgiveness to others, even up to 77 times if necessary.

14:15.334 --> 14:16.936
Do you need to forgive someone today?

14:17.517 --> 14:24.146
Why don't you commit to the Lord today that you will reach out to that person this week and you will extend that forgiveness?

14:26.402 --> 14:29.246
What about our words, using our words wisely?

14:30.548 --> 14:32.491
James warns us about the power of the tongue.

14:32.912 --> 14:35.356
I'll just quote a small passage from James 3 and 10.

14:36.137 --> 14:41.485
From the same mouth come blessing and cursing, my brothers, these things ought not to be so.

14:43.148 --> 14:45.391
We've got to be careful what way we use our words.

14:45.511 --> 14:51.621
We want to reciprocate the love of God to others, and words are important in how we do that.

14:51.641 --> 14:55.186
Do you need to apologize to someone this morning for the way you've spoken to them?

14:55.618 --> 14:58.082
Why don't you commit to God to do that this week?

14:58.102 --> 15:11.861
2 Corinthians 13 and 11, this is Paul speaking, aim for restoration, comfort one another, agree with one another, live in peace and the God of love and peace will be with you.

15:14.565 --> 15:20.874
When we're reciprocating the love of God, we wanna turn our attention out to the unbeliever, how do we reach the lost?

15:22.476 --> 15:23.698
You know, there's one method

15:23.842 --> 15:26.845
Again, this is not a popular method for reaching the lost.

15:27.485 --> 15:34.532
You won't find it trending online, but it is simply to love one another as our brothers and sisters in Christ.

15:35.933 --> 15:43.961
John 1335 says, by this, all men will know that you are my disciples if you have love one for another.

15:44.782 --> 15:51.548
I think the unsaved will notice something special about us if we can love one another without amazing love that God's given us.

15:52.389 --> 15:53.810
They might even listen to us.

15:54.050 --> 15:57.774
if we can learn how to show that love to one another.

15:59.616 --> 16:04.782
So we've talked about receiving God's love, stepping over the barriers of inadequacy of condemnation.

16:05.362 --> 16:09.106
We've talked about reciprocating the love of God to the Lord and to others.

16:09.707 --> 16:12.550
And I want to talk to you about resting in this love.

16:13.151 --> 16:19.698
And the setting is when we fail, when we're processing personal sin,

16:20.290 --> 16:22.173
We can be disrupted from rest.

16:22.433 --> 16:28.702
The enemy wants to pull us out of that place of rest, where we're resting in his love and in his grace, whenever we fail.

16:29.323 --> 16:42.002
But we have a promise, in Romans 8, 37, 39, know in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us, for I'm sure that neither death nor life nor angels nor rulers

16:42.210 --> 16:53.542
nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers, nor height, nor depth, nor anything else in creation will be able to separate us from the love of God in Christ Jesus our Lord.

16:53.962 --> 16:57.365
Don't allow anything to separate you from God's love.

16:58.467 --> 17:05.714
But personal sin in particular is something that can try to rob us of that unconditional love of God.

17:06.074 --> 17:08.357
And it pulls us from a place of rest.

17:08.417 --> 17:09.618
And God doesn't want that.

17:09.890 --> 17:15.597
He wants us to come before Him in honesty and openness and brokenness and share our heart with Him.

17:16.658 --> 17:19.281
It's His kindness that leads us to repentance.

17:20.363 --> 17:26.991
And King David knows all about the love of God and he knows all about sin.

17:27.912 --> 17:33.999
He did love God deeply and God loved Him and He did sin grievously through adultery, through murder.

17:35.101 --> 17:39.506
And in Psalm 51 we can see David's personal prayer to God.

17:41.122 --> 17:42.483
And he cries out to the Lord.

17:44.386 --> 17:45.927
And he asks God to change his heart.

17:46.808 --> 17:48.070
He acknowledges his sin.

17:50.392 --> 17:52.495
And he turns his acknowledgment into praise.

17:53.095 --> 17:55.858
And he turns his praise into openness and brokenness.

17:56.399 --> 18:00.243
And he turns that into a prayer for healing and a prayer to serve once again.

18:00.283 --> 18:03.547
And it's a model for us when we face personal sin.

18:03.607 --> 18:05.889
We don't run from God.

18:06.170 --> 18:10.194
We don't have the enemy that's not just away from God's love, but we rest.

18:10.498 --> 18:14.323
We rest in the love of God, as King David did.

18:16.146 --> 18:26.400
Let me read the end of Psalm 51, just before the end of it, in fact, where David says to the Lord, oh Lord, open my lips, and my mouth will declare your praise.

18:26.760 --> 18:29.484
For you will not delight in sacrifice, or I would give it.

18:29.945 --> 18:31.787
You will not be pleased with burnt offering.

18:32.348 --> 18:39.538
The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit, a broken and contrite, heart, oh God, you will not despise.

18:41.570 --> 18:44.273
In this setting, God doesn't want sacrifice.

18:44.313 --> 18:46.214
He doesn't want more giving and more serving.

18:46.615 --> 18:47.916
He wants brokenness.

18:47.996 --> 18:49.197
He wants to hear your heart.

18:50.138 --> 19:02.049
If you're going to stay in rest when it comes to the ups and downs of your life, you've got to be open and fluid before the Lord, not just a kind of mechanical relationship where we say, sorry, Lord, I blew it.

19:03.230 --> 19:05.292
I just want forgiveness and I just want to move on.

19:06.594 --> 19:11.218
No, He wants us to pour our heart out to Him to acknowledge our sin, but then

19:11.650 --> 19:16.059
to turn that introspection into praise, to turn it up to him.

19:16.119 --> 19:31.730
They're not just continually look inwardly until they're so depressed with ourselves, but to, yes, acknowledge our sin, but turn that acknowledgement to God in praise, as David did, and lead into brokenness, and openness,

19:32.226 --> 19:40.477
A vulnerability before God where he's able to come in and heal us from whatever those hurts or whatever has been bothering us, that God would heal us.

19:40.497 --> 19:44.443
He'd build those walls of our life back up so we'd be able to serve him again.

19:44.483 --> 19:54.356
And David points to that part at the end of his prayer when he says to the Lord, do good to Zion in your good pleasure, build up the walls of Jerusalem.

19:54.917 --> 20:01.426
Then you will delight in sacrifices, in burnt offerings and whole offerings, bulls will be offered on your altar.

20:01.954 --> 20:08.421
There comes a time again for serving, forgiving, but it has to be out of that place of wholeness.

20:08.442 --> 20:09.783
In fact, it doesn't have to be.

20:10.083 --> 20:23.038
And that's why you see many Christians falling in great sin or burning out in serving God or in ministry and life, because they're serving and they're giving and they're offering, but there's no source of power.

20:23.058 --> 20:25.221
There's no source of strength, the love of God.

20:25.261 --> 20:27.544
They're not taking time to rest in His love.

20:28.184 --> 20:29.586
They're not receiving His love.

20:31.330 --> 20:33.753
And there's nothing left in the tank, so to speak.

20:35.215 --> 20:42.084
We're to learn how to rest in his love, even in personal sin, to rest in his love, to allow that healing to take place.

20:42.184 --> 20:45.168
And then from a place of wholeness, we can serve once again.

20:45.208 --> 20:47.051
We can offer sacrifices to God.

20:47.451 --> 20:51.096
We can give offerings to God once again, when the time is right.

20:53.058 --> 20:58.866
And the final point I want to make this morning is about reveling in the love of God.

20:59.746 --> 21:05.432
As we put all of this together this morning, it brings us to a place where we can revel in the love of God.

21:06.713 --> 21:16.404
We can comprehend how wide and how high and how long and just how deep is his love as we spoke about in Ephesians 3 at the start this morning.

21:18.125 --> 21:26.354
This is about the revelation of his love becoming an impartation from God, where

21:26.562 --> 21:55.826
through his power, through the power of the Holy Spirit, were strengthened by his love, where his love begins to set us free from anxiety, from fear, where the revelation of his love sets us free from depression, from loneliness, from rejection, to revel in his love and to be filled with his love can give us a sense of connectedness with the family of God, which is something that

21:56.738 --> 21:59.182
we need and we should desire to have.

22:02.086 --> 22:20.094
You know, I think when we really begin to revel in His love and walk in His love and reciprocate His love, we really begin to see our fellow believers as brothers and sisters in Christ, not just as other people or, you know, other believers, but we really get a sense of, that is my brother and that is my sister right there.

22:20.554 --> 22:21.896
And then we treat them with love.

22:23.719 --> 22:25.682
Traveling in His love is where we live.

22:26.050 --> 22:39.163
every day with an expectation of his return, that we're gonna meet him, that we're gonna celebrate with him, that we're gonna be his bride, the church, that we're gonna be lost in his love for all of eternity.

22:40.284 --> 22:42.586
God's love is alive in you this morning.

22:45.169 --> 22:54.898
If you know Christ, if you know this love that I'm talking about, if you've received it, we learn how to reciprocate it.

22:55.618 --> 23:03.086
to rest in it and to revel in it, then you watch how the love of God will revolutionize your life.

23:05.268 --> 23:09.092
If you haven't put faith in Jesus Christ, I urge you to do it.

23:09.132 --> 23:10.494
I urge you to do it now.

23:11.895 --> 23:18.062
I can pray for you now and you can put faith in Jesus Christ and in this great love today.

23:18.102 --> 23:25.490
I'm gonna pray a prayer and I ask you to follow me in this prayer if you want to give your life to the Lord Jesus.

23:25.826 --> 23:26.126
today.

23:27.768 --> 23:29.070
Remember this is your prayer.

23:30.371 --> 23:31.773
Pray these words with me.

23:33.455 --> 23:36.679
Lord God, I confess I am a sinner.

23:39.042 --> 23:40.223
I need to be saved.

23:42.466 --> 23:43.888
Jesus, you are the answer.

23:45.830 --> 23:47.492
You gave your life for my sins.

23:50.736 --> 23:52.358
You rose again from the grave.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.602
You are alive today.

23:57.058 --> 23:58.400
I ask you to forgive me.

24:00.562 --> 24:02.405
Make my spirit come to life.

24:04.127 --> 24:10.835
Ground me a place in heaven so that when I die, I will know for sure that I will be with you.

24:10.875 --> 24:18.925
Today, I start a brand new life, alive in you.

24:20.547 --> 24:22.069
Amen.

24:22.089 --> 24:26.354
If you prayed that prayer this morning and you meant it, you've taken the first step

24:26.530 --> 24:28.893
in becoming a follower of Jesus.

24:28.913 --> 24:30.574
And there's a few things that I would urge you to do.

24:31.756 --> 24:32.677
Tell someone about it.

24:34.679 --> 24:38.603
Find a Bible believing church, whether that's local, whether that's online.

24:38.683 --> 24:40.525
Connect with fellow Christians.

24:41.226 --> 24:44.229
Start reading a Bible and pray.

24:44.570 --> 24:51.317
Talk to the Lord because the Lord hears you and we'd love to hear from you if you've made that decision this morning.

24:51.477 --> 24:55.021
Visit our website, go to our contact office page and just drop us a message.

24:55.401 --> 24:56.082
God bless you.

24:56.546 --> 24:59.129
Thank you, Church, for tuning in this morning.

24:59.189 --> 25:00.090
Thank you for listening.

25:00.671 --> 25:03.534
And I hope that that has inspired you, that has encouraged you.

25:04.335 --> 25:08.621
I pray that the love of God would come alive in you in a greater way.

25:08.661 --> 25:11.544
Let me read Ephesians 3, 16.

25:11.564 --> 25:13.807
One more time to end this morning.

25:15.829 --> 25:22.898
I pray that God's glorious, unlimited resources will empower you with inner strength through his spirit.

25:23.490 --> 25:27.135
Then Christ will make His home in your hearts as you trust in Him.

25:27.736 --> 25:30.861
Your roots will go down into God's love and keep you strong.

25:31.482 --> 25:40.215
And may you have the power to understand, as all God's people should, how wide, how long, how high and how deep His love is.

25:40.976 --> 25:45.883
May you experience the love of Christ, though it's too great to fully understand.

25:46.504 --> 25:53.074
Then you will be made complete with all the fullness of life and power that comes from God.

25:53.698 --> 25:56.628
and we hope to see you next week.

25:56.648 --> 25:57.618
God bless.

